It is a secondary neuron of the 14B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil and sends output to the abdominal neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the metathoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
